---
By: Eliphas Levi
Locus:
  Page: 31
  Verse: 11
Tags:
  - Beauty
---
Passing beauties are only the fugitive reflections of the eternal. ...All
beauty alters and all life melts away; in short, everything passes with
marvelous rapidity; beautiful Helen (of Troy) has become a toothless skull,
then a handful of dust, then nothing.
